      <lg xml:id="TolE0280">
<l>aikāra viṟutip peyarnilai muṉṉar</l>
<l>vēṟṟumai yāyiṉ valleḻuttu mikumē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If it means <foreign xml:lang="ta">peṟṟam</foreign> ' bull ', it is necessary [that it is</l>
<l>followed] by full <foreign xml:lang="ta">iṉ.</foreign><note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">cē</foreign> has two meanings ; if it refers to a
          tree, it follows the rule of the nasal, if it refers to a bull, it receives the empty-morph <foreign xml:lang="ta">-in : cē-v-iṉ-kōṭu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
